feat: complete KIPRIS prior-art search with KR patent survey

Add KIPRIS Plus OpenAPI keyword search automation and identify 4 KR
patents (KR10-2875492, KR10-2765780, KR2022-0046292, KR10-2576380)
relevant to QR multi-layer encoding. None match QoverwRap's logical
payload-layer + embedded Ed25519 signature + role-based Resolver
combination — novelty hypothesis reinforced.

Constraint: KIPRIS Plus requires live subscription; endpoint and
  ServiceKey param name differ from 2020 Java sample
Rejected: Guessing endpoint from Java sample only | 404s — live probe
  revealed /kipo-api/kipi/ base + ServiceKey (not accessKey) param
Confidence: high
Scope-risk: narrow
Directive: Use inventionTitle field over word for signal; word-field
  hits are noisy (thousands) dominated by unrelated "QR decomposition"
  MIMO patents
Not-tested: CNIPA, J-PlatPat, INPI searches (§6-2~6-4 remain open)
EOF
)" 2>&1 | tail -20
